# Aether Environment Variables

# GitHub Deployment Configuration
# Required for deploying projects to GitHub as encrypted JSON files
# 
# To obtain a GitHub Personal Access Token:
# 1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. Click "Generate new token" (classic)
# 3. Give it a descriptive name (e.g., "Alov Deployment")
# 4. Select scopes: "repo" (Full control of private repositories)
# 5. Click "Generate token" and copy the token immediately
# 6. Paste the token below as GITHUB_TOKEN
#
# Create a repository for storing deployed projects:
# 1. Go to https://github.com/new
# 2. Create a new repository (can be public or private)
# 3. Use the repository owner as GITHUB_OWNER
# 4. Use the repository name as GITHUB_REPO

GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_personal_access_token_here
GITHUB_OWNER=your_github_username_or_org
GITHUB_REPO=your_repository_name
GITHUB_BRANCH=main

# Note: Without these configured, deployment features will not work.
# However, users can still:
# - Download projects as ZIP
# - Push to GitHub manually
# - Export projects
